   "source": [
    "### âœï¸ Invariant Check (write your answer here)\n",
    "- Pick one non-tip row (a row with **two** `*`). Explain why the **width invariant** holds for that row:\n",
    "  - Why is the first `*` placed correctly?\n",
    "  - Why does the second `*` land symmetrically?\n",
    "- Explain why the "tip row" (one `*`) is a necessary special case.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**My answers:**\n",
    "\n",
    "Taking row 1 (second row from top) in a height=9 diamond as example:\n",
    "- `leading_spaces = mid - row = 4 - 1 = 3`\n",
    "- `inner_spaces = 2*row - 1 = 2*1 - 1 = 1`\n",
    "\n",
    "The first `*` is placed correctly because leading_spaces is calculated from the midpoint. As row increases, we get closer to the widest part, so leading spaces decrease.\n",
    "\n",
    "The second `*` lands symmetrically because inner_spaces grows by 2 each row. So the total width of \"* + inner + *\" expands evenly on both sides. The formula `2*row - 1` gives us 1, 3, 5, 7... which keeps everything centered.\n",
    "\n",
    "The tip row needs special handling because at row=0, the formula `2*row - 1 = -1` gives negative inner spaces. You cant have negative spaces between stars, so we just print one star instead of two. Its the point of the diamond where the two edges meet."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
