    "\n",
    "`dist = abs(mid - row)` creates symmetry because the absolute value makes the distance the same whether youre above or below the midpoint. Row 0 and row 8 (in height=9) both have dist=4. Row 1 and row 7 both have dist=3. The abs() function mirrors everything around the middle automatically.\n",
    "\n",
    "`inner_spaces < 0` means were at a tip of the diamond. The inner space formula is based on how far we are from the tip - at the tip itself theres no \"inside\" to the diamond yet, the two edges havent separated. Negative inner spaces is mathematically saying \"these two stars havent split apart yet\" so we just draw one star instead."
   ]
